========================================================================
JACOBSTHAL NUMBERS IN TOURNAMENT THEORY
========================================================================

--- 1. The Jacobsthal Sequence ---
J(n) = J(n-1) + 2·J(n-2)
J(0) = 0, J(1) = 1
Closed form: J(n) = (2^n - (-1)^n) / 3

n:  J(n)   2^n   J(n)/2^n    (2^n-(-1)^n)/3
 0:        0         1  0.000000         0  ✓
 1:        1         2  0.500000         1  ✓
 2:        1         4  0.250000         1  ✓
 3:        3         8  0.375000         3  ✓
 4:        5        16  0.312500         5  ✓
 5:       11        32  0.343750        11  ✓
 6:       21        64  0.328125        21  ✓
 7:       43       128  0.335938        43  ✓
 8:       85       256  0.332031        85  ✓
 9:      171       512  0.333984       171  ✓
10:      341      1024  0.333008       341  ✓
11:      683      2048  0.333496       683  ✓
12:     1365      4096  0.333252      1365  ✓
13:     2731      8192  0.333374      2731  ✓
14:     5461     16384  0.333313      5461  ✓
15:    10923     32768  0.333344     10923  ✓
16:    21845     65536  0.333328     21845  ✓
17:    43691    131072  0.333336     43691  ✓
18:    87381    262144  0.333332     87381  ✓
19:   174763    524288  0.333334    174763  ✓

J(n)/J(n-1) ratios (should → 2):
  J(2)/J(1) = 1.000000
  J(3)/J(2) = 3.000000
  J(4)/J(3) = 1.666667
  J(5)/J(4) = 2.200000
  J(6)/J(5) = 1.909091
  J(7)/J(6) = 2.047619
  J(8)/J(7) = 1.976744
  J(9)/J(8) = 2.011765
  J(10)/J(9) = 1.994152
  J(11)/J(10) = 2.002933
  J(12)/J(11) = 1.998536
  J(13)/J(12) = 2.000733
  J(14)/J(13) = 1.999634

--- 2. Jacobsthal-Lucas Companion ---
j(n) = j(n-1) + 2·j(n-2)
j(0) = 2, j(1) = 1
Closed form: j(n) = 2^n + (-1)^n
(Same recurrence, different initial conditions)

n:  j(n)    2^n    j(n)-2^n
 0:      2       1   +1
 1:      1       2   -1
 2:      5       4   +1
 3:      7       8   -1
 4:     17      16   +1
 5:     31      32   -1
 6:     65      64   +1
 7:    127     128   -1
 8:    257     256   +1
 9:    511     512   -1
10:   1025    1024   +1
11:   2047    2048   -1
12:   4097    4096   +1
13:   8191    8192   -1
14:  16385   16384   +1

NOTE: j(n) = 2^n + (-1)^n = 2^n ± 1
  These are the MERSENNE ± 1 numbers!
  j(n) - J(n) = (2^n+(-1)^n)/1 - (2^n-(-1)^n)/3
              = 2·(2^n+2·(-1)^n)/3

